								<a name="content"></a><h3>Section Introduction</h3>
								<hr>
								<p class="lead">In this section, you will learn the basic terminology and skills for creating documents using word processing software.</p>
								<p>You will also gain a fundamental understanding of how word processing software works in order to be an empowered user of the technology.</p>
								<p>You will learn to control default settings and options in the word processing program instead of letting the program defaults to control how you create documents. By understanding the program controls in word processing, you will be able to explore program defaults and options in other programs you encounter.</p>
								<p>Knowing about these settings, defaults and options lowers your &ldquo;hassle factor&rdquo; in dealing with software. In word processing, these defaults and options affect the way your information looks. You will also apply what you learned in the Files and Folders section, by selecting both the location and the file extension of each new document you create.</p>
								<h6><i>This is important for two reasons.</i></h6>
								<br />
								<p><strong>Word Processing is everywhere.</strong> <br />At most every workplace and in most every school, you are expected to know how to create and documents using a computer. In order to do this, you must know the basics of using word processing software.</p>
								<p><strong>Word Processing is a basic skill.</strong>  <br />Creating and saving documents is one of the most basic tasks you can do using a computer. Because of this, mastering these skills will help you to learn and understand other skills, like spreadsheets, more easily.</p>
								<p>With the information you learn here, you can be a more knowledgeable and empowered user of your computer and its basic software.</p>
